00:00:04.190 --> 00:00:06.765
What's a div block?

00:00:06.765 --> 00:00:12.060
Well, I do blog is the most
basic blocks on a web page.

00:00:12.060 --> 00:00:14.085
If you go to the Add section,

00:00:14.085 --> 00:00:17.190
you can see that we have
different sections here we

00:00:17.190 --> 00:00:20.910
have layout, basic
topography, etc.

00:00:20.910 --> 00:00:24.690
And under the basic section
we have different elements.

00:00:24.690 --> 00:00:27.300
And the first one is
called div block.

00:00:27.300 --> 00:00:30.690
If I try to drag and
drop it into my Canvas,

00:00:30.690 --> 00:00:32.190
you can see that the DFF block

00:00:32.190 --> 00:00:34.035
has been added to
my canvas here,

00:00:34.035 --> 00:00:37.260
and it takes up the whole
width of the canvas.

00:00:37.260 --> 00:00:39.510
A def block actually is sized

00:00:39.510 --> 00:00:41.885
based on that content inside.

00:00:41.885 --> 00:00:43.400
However, here, as you can see,

00:00:43.400 --> 00:00:45.680
it created a boundary
and it seems

00:00:45.680 --> 00:00:48.530
that there is a
some space inside.

00:00:48.530 --> 00:00:50.540
However, if I preview that,

00:00:50.540 --> 00:00:53.195
if I just click on this icon,

00:00:53.195 --> 00:00:55.115
you can see that
nothing is here.

00:00:55.115 --> 00:00:57.320
It's actually an empty box.

00:00:57.320 --> 00:00:59.570
It's a dynamic bikes
because when you

00:00:59.570 --> 00:01:01.985
add more and more
elements into it,

00:01:01.985 --> 00:01:04.325
it's size will be
changed accordingly.

00:01:04.325 --> 00:01:05.765
So let's give it a try.

00:01:05.765 --> 00:01:07.865
I'm going to go
ahead and try to add

00:01:07.865 --> 00:01:10.505
a heading into this diblock.

00:01:10.505 --> 00:01:12.950
Just like that. Now, I'm

00:01:12.950 --> 00:01:15.065
gonna go ahead and
add a paragraph.

00:01:15.065 --> 00:01:16.280
There we go.

00:01:16.280 --> 00:01:19.865
And let me go ahead
and add a button.

00:01:19.865 --> 00:01:21.470
Okay, cool.

00:01:21.470 --> 00:01:25.295
Now these three elements
are inside this div block.

00:01:25.295 --> 00:01:26.435
And as you can see,

00:01:26.435 --> 00:01:29.960
that def block size has
been changed accordingly.

00:01:29.960 --> 00:01:32.629
If I remove one of
these elements,

00:01:32.629 --> 00:01:35.855
you can see that the def
block size has been changed.

00:01:35.855 --> 00:01:38.855
Again, a def block
generally can be anything.

00:01:38.855 --> 00:01:40.385
It could be an image,

00:01:40.385 --> 00:01:42.020
it could be a line.

00:01:42.020 --> 00:01:45.695
But most of the time we use
a div block in order to

00:01:45.695 --> 00:01:50.150
align elements and group
elements together, e.g.

00:01:50.150 --> 00:01:53.090
here we group these
two elements together.

00:01:53.090 --> 00:01:56.300
And whenever we
want to modify e.g.

00:01:56.300 --> 00:01:59.480
the margin of this
particular div block,

00:01:59.480 --> 00:02:01.910
we can just head over
to this pasting section

00:02:01.910 --> 00:02:03.815
on the Stein panel here.

00:02:03.815 --> 00:02:04.700
E.g. I.

00:02:04.700 --> 00:02:07.760
Can set the top margin to 70.

00:02:07.760 --> 00:02:08.810
And there we go.

00:02:08.810 --> 00:02:11.270
Both these elements
have been moved because

00:02:11.270 --> 00:02:13.790
